│ ├── src/
│ ├── package.json
│ └── .env.example
├── .gitignore


---

## ⚙Tech Stack

- **Frontend**: React, Vite, TypeScript, TailwindCSS, ShadCN/UI  
- **Backend**: Node.js, Express.js, MongoDB, JWT  
- **AI**: Google Gemini API (`generateContent` endpoint for summaries, tags, and Q&A)  
- **Auth**: JWT with user/admin roles  

---

## Setup Instructions

### 1. Clone Repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/knowledgehub.git
cd knowledgehub
cd backend
npm install
cp .env.example .env  
npm run dev
                            
env variable
PORT=4000
MONGO_URI=your-mongodb-uri
JWT_SECRET=your-secret
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d

AI_API_KEY=your-gemini-api-key
AI_API_URL=https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models/gemini-2.5-flash-preview-05-20:generateContent

#frontend setup
cd ../frontend
npm install
cp .env.example .env  
npm run dev
                             
